H.  David Kotz , the inspector general
of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, is leaving the
agency at the end of the month to join a private investigative
services firm, the SEC said.  Kotz plans to join Gryphon Strategies as a managing
director in its Washington office, the SEC said in a  statement .
He plans to focus on conducting corporate fraud investigations
as well as assisting whistleblowers in exposing fraud and
improving government accountability, according to the SEC.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
